HEADWORD: Cedrat
<hw>Ce"drat</hw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧"dr⟦acr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>c⟦eacute⟧drat</ets>. See <er>Cedar</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Properly the citron, a variety of <spn>Citrus medica</spn>, with
large fruits, not acid, and having a high perfume.</def>⟦br⟧
